frameDefinitions: A Speaker succeeds in getting an Addressee to believe or plan to execute the Content the Speaker has in mind.
In this frame either a Stimulus brings about a particular emotion or experience in the Experiencer or  saliently fails to bring about a particular experience.
An Entity aids in the successful completion of a Purpose.
This frame contains words which name permanent fixed structures forming an enclosure and providing protection from the elements.
A Benefactor confers a Beneficial_situation to a Beneficiary.
This frame contains words for individuals as viewed in terms of their age.
frameExamples: At one point, Walter tries to <t>convince</t> his wife that he has had a story accepted by BBC Radio.
A box is an <t>ideal</t> storage device.
The baroque <t>church</t>, built in 1635, has a very rich interior
His presence at the summit did not <t>BENEFIT</t> diplomatic relations in the slightest.
listRoleDefinitions: The person that the Speaker seeks to influence to act.
The person who intends through the use of language to get another person to act.
The wish for action on the <fen>Addressee</fen>'s part that the <fen>Speaker</fen> expresses.
A piece of written or spoken material that changes the mind of the <fen>Addressee</fen>.
The general item or items that are the focus of the <fen>Content</fen> of the <fen>Speaker</fen>'s message.
The location where the Speaker suades the Addressee.
The <fen>Stimulus</fen> is the object or event which brings about the emotion in the <fen>Experiencer</fen>.
The item which is useful for some purpose.
The kind of task which is promoted by the use or presence of the <fen>Entity</fen>.
When the <fen>Entity</fen> is useful for a <fen>Purpose</fen>.
The entity built by the <fen>Builder</fen> which has some <fen>Function</fen>.
The <fen>Benefactor</fen> is the person or thing that gives an advantage to the <fen>Beneficiary</fen>.
The <fen>Beneficiary</fen> is person or thing that receives an advantage from the <fen>Benefactor</fen>.

The <fen>Beneficial_situation</fen> is the item or action that is given to or done for the <fen>Beneficiary</fen> by the <fen>Benefactor</fen>.  A change of possession can, but does not have to occur.
The human being of a certain age.
The <fen>Age</fen> is the length of time the <fen>Person</fen> has been alive.
listRoleExamples: <fex>His speech</fex> convinced me to join the Peace Corps.
You haven't convinced me <fex>about that yet</fex>.
